Title   : UltraTech plans fresh capex of ₹10,255 cr
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-10-18T09:49:14
Fetched : 2025-10-18T18:39:43.867211
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/ultratech-plans-fresh-capex-of-10255-cr/article70178751.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
UltraTech Cement, an Aditya Birla Group company, has announced a fresh capex of ₹10,255 crore to expand its cement production capacity by 22.8 mtpa, including that of its subsidiary India Cements.
The investment plan was approved by the Board of Directors at its meeting held here on Saturday.
It will be executed through a mix of brownfield and greenfield projects.
Commercial production from these new capacities is expected to go fully on stream in a phased manner, starting from FY28 and will catapult the company’s cement capacity to 240.76 mtpa globally.
Over the past decade, UltraTech has added over 65 mtpa capacity through the inorganic growth.
Kumar Mangalam Birla, Chairman, Aditya Birla Group said the latest capacity expansion follows over ₹50,000 crore invested over the past five years.
The investment reflects the company’s confidence in the Indian economy and the scale of its infrastructure ambitions, he said.
When capital is deployed strategically, it energises ecosystems, deepens industrial linkages and creates durable employment, he added.
As India enters a transformative era of infrastructure and economic development, UltraTech is well-positioned to meet the rising demand for cement, he said.
Published on October 18, 2025

Title   : Dixon Technologies net profit jumps 86% to ₹746 crore in September quarter
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-10-18T05:16:28
Fetched : 2025-10-18T18:39:43.867264
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/dixon-technologies-net-profit-jumps-86-to-746-crore-in-september-quarter/article70178184.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Electronics manufacturing services firm Dixon Technologies has posted an 81 per cent jump in consolidated net profit to ₹745.7 crore in the second quarter ended September 30, 2025, according to an exchange filing.
The company had reported a net profit of ₹411.7 crore in the same period a year ago.
The revenue from operations of the company grew by 28.7 per cent to ₹14,855 crore during the reported quarter from ₹11,534 crore in the September 2024 quarter.
The mobile devices manufacturing division of the company contributed 90 per cent of revenue during the reported quarter, while 6 per cent came from the consumer electronics and appliances division.
The Nomination and Remuneration Committee of the company has approved the grant of 7,000 number of stock options to the employees of the company, its Subsidiary company(ies) and Joint Venture Company(ies) from time to time in one or more tranches.
Published on October 18, 2025

